doc.ContractDescription: NASA FLOOD RESPONSE WORKSHOP FLOODING IS ONE OF THE COSTLIEST NATURAL DISASTERS AND BY 2050 COSTS OF FLOODS IN COASTAL CITIES ALONE ARE PREDICTED TO REACH $1 TRILLION ANNUALLY (HALLEGATE ET AL., 2013). RECENTLY, ALL AROUND THE WORLD, FLOODS HAVE BEEN OF EXCEPTIONALLY HIGH MAGNITUDE WITH RAINFALLS EXCEEDING RECORD AMOUNTS AS WELL AS CAUSING UNPRECEDENTED DAMAGE IN MANY COUNTRIES. RECENT EVENTS HAVE COVERED SPATIAL SCALES WELL BEYOND WHAT WE HAVE SEEN IN THE PAST AND ARE FREQUENTLY SURPASSING TRADITIONAL REGIONAL DISASTER RESPONSE COVERAGE. IN ESSENCE, THESE LARGE SCALE EVENTS HAVE DEMONSTRATED THAT THERE IS A NEED TO ACHIEVE A GLOBAL RESPONSE IN A VERY LIMITED AMOUNT OF TIME, SO THAT RELIEF TEAMS AND DECISION-MAKERS CAN ACT QUICKLY AND AGENCIES AS WELL AS INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS CAN DEAL SWIFTLY WITH SUCCESSIVE BIG EVENTS AND DELIVER RELEVANT GEOSPATIAL DATA AND FLOOD IMAGERY WHEN AND WHERE NEEDED ALL AROUND THE WORLD. IN THE CASE OF FLOOD MONITORING AND RESPONSE, NASA ALREADY PROVIDES A NUMBER OF SERVICES AS WELL AS IMAGE AND COMPUTER SIMULATION PRODUCTS DURING AN EVENT, EITHER THROUGH ONGOING ACTIVITIES AT NASA CENTERS OR THROUGH NASA PROJECT FUNDING, ALL OF WHICH NEED BE MAINTAINED AND SUSTAINED. IT IS DIFFICULT TO COORDINATE ALL OF THOSE SYSTEMS DURING ONE SINGLE EVENT, LET ALONE MULTIPLE SIMULTANEOUS EVENTS OR SUCCESSIVE LARGE EVENTS. ALSO, EACH OF THOSE SYSTEMS PROVIDES A UNIQUE CAPABILITY AND SO GLOBAL COORDINATION IS NECESSARY AND THERE IS PROBABLY NO NEED TO DEVELOP (YET) ANOTHER SYSTEM BEFORE SUCH A COORDINATION TAKES PLACE. HENCE, THERE IS A NEED FOR A FLOOD RESPONSE WORKSHOP. THIS WORKSHOP WOULD BRING TOGETHER VARIOUS PIS AND LEAD PEOPLE FROM NASAS FLOOD EXPERT POOL TO DISCUSS AND FORMALIZE A GLOBAL FLOOD RESPONSE TO LARGE EVENTS A WORKSHOP PROGRAM COMMITTEE WILL ALSO NEED TO DISCUSS HOW TO BRING IN NEW PARTNERSHIPS WITH THE WATER AND FLOOD COMMUNITIES POSSIBLY INCLUDING THE NATIONAL WATER CENTER, NOAA RIVER FORECAST CENTERS, USACE ON TRANS-BOUNDARY FLOOD AND INSURANCE COMPANIES ON FLOOD RISK, ETC., AND ALSO INVOLVING THE WORLD BANK (ALTHOUGH SCALABILITY OF THEIR SINGLE COUNTRY PARADIGMS WILL BE A SIGNIFICANT CHALLENGE TO ADDRESS). THE PLANNED FLOOD RESPONSE WORKSHOP SHOULD NOT BE A SCIENCE MEETING NOR A RESEARCH REVIEW; RATHER IT SHOULD BE A PRO-ACTIVE DISCUSSION WITH FOLLOW-ON ACTIONS ON HOW TO PROCEED TO BUILD A COORDINATED AND INTEROPERABLE RESPONSE TO FLOOD DISASTERS AND EMERGENCIES.

doc.ContractDescription: ON THE EFFICIENCY OF MAGNETIC RECONNECTION AT THE MAGNETOPAUSE. WHEN THE RECONNECTION RATE IS HIGH, LARGE AMOUNTS OF ENERGY AND MASS ARE TRANSFERRED FROM THE SOLAR WIND TO THE MAGNETOSPHERE. THE PLASMASPHERIC PLUME IS ONE FEATURE THAT MAY LIMIT THIS THE OVERARCHING GOAL OF THIS STUDY IS TO QUANTIFY HOW THE PLASMASPHERIC PLUME IMPACTS RECONNECTION AND SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERIC COUPLING. COUPLING PROCESS. DURING GEOMAGNETICALLY QUITE TIMES, THE POPULATION OF COLD, DENSE, CHARGED PARTICLES COMPOSING THE PLASMASPHERE EXB DRIFT ON CLOSED PATHS WITHIN A RADIAL DISTANCE OF ....... 4.5 RE AROUND THE EARTH. DMING MORE DISTURBED TIMES OF STRONG SOLAR WIND DRIVING, AN ENHANCED CONVECTION ELECTRIC FIELD CAN CAUSE SOME OF THE DENSE PLASMASPHERE TO FORM A TONGUE OR PLUME EXTENDING SUNWARD TOWARDS THE DAYSIDE MAGNETOPAUSE. WHEN THE PLUME IS IN THE VICINITY OF THE SUBSOLAR MAGNETOPAUSE, THE DENSITY CAN INCREASE FROM A NOMINAL VALUE OF ,...,0 .L CM 3 BY THREE ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE TO ,..., 100 CM 3 . THEORY PREDICTS THE LOCAL RECONNECTION RATE TO BE INVERSELY PROPORTIONAL TO .J DENSITY. ALL OTHER VARIABLES REMAINING THE SAME, INCREASING THE DENSITY BY LOOOX FROM THE PRESENCE OF THE PLUME WOULD DECREASE THE MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION RATE BY A FACTOR OF 32. AN EQUALLY IMPORTANT ASPECT OF THIS ISSUE TO BE ADDRESSED IN THIS STUDY IS SPATIALLY BOW LARGE IS A PLUME AS IT CONTACTS THE MAGNETOPAUSE? DECREASING THE RECONNECTION RATE BY SUCH A DEGREE WOULD HAVE A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON THE TRANSFER OF ENERGY FROM THE SOLAR WIND TO THE MAGNETOSPHERE. THIS WOULD LIMIT THE GENERATION OF STORMS, SUBSTORMS, AS WELL AS OTHER GEOMAGNETIC DISTURBANCES. A PLUME WOULD ALSO BE ACTIVE IN CONTROLLING HOW GEOEFFECTIVE CERTAIN SOLAR WIND STRUCTURES ARE. IN ADDITION TO THE GLOBAL MAGNETOSPHERIC PICTURE, THIS PROBLEM ALSO PROVIDES A USEFUL PLATFO1M TO STUDY THE MICROPHYSICS OF RECONNECTION. THE CUFFENT STUDY WILL MONITOR CHANGES IN RECONNECTION AND OTHER FORMS OF SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERE COUPLING WITH THE THEMIS SPACECRAFT. CAREFUL INSPECTION OF MAGNETOPAUSE OF SOLAR WIND-MAGNETOSPHERE COUPLING WITH AND WITHOUT HIGH DENSITY PLUME MATERIAL WILL ALLOW THE TEAM TO STUDY THE IMPACT OF CHANGING DENSITY SEVERAL ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE ON THESE MECHANISMS. THE STUDY IS TIMELY AS IT PROVIDES IMPORTANT INPUT FOR UNDERSTANDING THE VAN ALLEN PROBE AND THEMIS DATA. SINCE A PLUME CAN CUT ACROSS ALL L-SHELLS, WAVES THAT OCCUR PREFERENTIALLY FOR HIGH DENSITY SUCH AS PLASMASPHERIC HISS, WHISTLER-MODE CHORUS, AND EMIC CAN ENERGIZE AND SCATTER RADIATION BELT PARTICLES OVER A WIDE RADIAL RANGE. THE PROPOSED STUDY ALSO ADDRESSES GOALS OF THE FORTHCOMING MMS MISSION TO UNDERSTAND HOW EFFICIENT RECONNECTION IS UNDER GREATLY DIFFERENT PLASMA REGIMES WITH AND WITHOUT HIGBDENSITY PLUMES.

SCIENCE GOALS AND OBJECTIVES THE CUSP PLASMA IMAGING DETECTOR (CUPID) CUBESAT WILL ANSWER LONGSTANDING QUESTIONS REGARDING THE MACROSCALE PROPERTIES OF MAGNETIC RECONNECTION SUCH AS, (I) WHAT IS THE LONGITUDINAL EXTENT OF THE RECONNECTING MAGNETOPAUSE; (II) UNDER WHAT CONDITIONS DO MULTIPLE RECONNECTION SITES FORM; AND (III) UNDER WHAT CONDITIONS IS RECONNECTION CONTINUOUS VERSUS BURSTY? THE PROCESS OF MAGNETIC RECONNECTION CHANGES MAGNETIC TOPOLOGY AND PERMITS THE FLOW OF ENERGY FROM THE SOLAR WIND INTO THE EARTH S MAGNETOSPHERE AND IONOSPHERE. THIS PROJECT HAS GREAT RELEVANCE FOR GOAL #2 OF THE NRC DECADAL SURVEY FOR SOLAR AND SPACE PHYSICS TO DETERMINE THE DYNAMICS AND COUPLING OF EARTHS MAGNETOSPHERE, IONOSPHERE, AND ATMOSPHERE AND THEIR RESPONSE TO SOLAR AND TERRESTRIAL INPUTS. IT CAN BE DIFFICULT TO DETERMINE THE GLOBAL NATURE OF MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION FROM ISOLATED IN-SITU SPACECRAFT MEASUREMENTS. EVEN CLUSTERS OF SPACECRAFT WITH INTER-SPACECRAFT SEPARATIONS RANGING FROM 10 S OF KILOMETERS (MMS) OR EVEN 1-2 RE (CLUSTER) CANNOT DETERMINE THE EXTENT (AND THEREFORE SIGNIFICANCE) OF PROCESSES THAT MAY SPAN 10 S OF RE. HOWEVER, THE MAGNETIC FIELD LINES ON WHICH RECONNECTION OCCURS CONVERGES IN THE CUSPS, WHERE OBSERVATIONS OF CUSP ION DISPERSIONS PROVIDE A RICH SOURCE OF INFORMATION ON THE CHARACTERISTICS OF RECONNECTION. HOWEVER INHERENT AMBIGUITY BETWEEN SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL FEATURES IN IN-SITU MEASUREMENTS HINDERS OUR ABILITY TO INTERPRET THESE OBSERVATIONS. THE CUPID OBSERVATORY WILL OVERCOME THE SPATIAL/TEMPORAL AMBIGUITY BY INNOVATIVELY IMAGING ION DISPERSIONS IN SOFT X-RAYS. SOFT X-RAYS ARE EMITTED FROM CHARGE-EXCHANGE BETWEEN HIGH-CHARGE-STATE SOLAR WIND AND NEUTRAL HYDROGEN ATOMS IN THE EARTHS GEOCORONA. BY IMAGING ION DISPERSIONS, ONE CAN MAP AND UNDERSTAND THE FULL SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL FEATURES OF ION INJECTIONS AND THEREFORE THE MACROSCALE NATURE OF MAGNETOPAUSE RECONNECTION. METHODOLOGY THE CUPID MISSION IS DESIGNED AROUND AN AUTONOMOUS, MAGNETORQUER-CONTROLLED 3U CUBESAT CARRYING AN X-RAY TELESCOPE. THE WIDE FIELD-OF-VIEW SOFT X-RAY TELESCOPE WILL FOCUS 0.1-2KEV PHOTONS WITH SLUMPED MICROPORE OPTICS ONTO A POSITION SENSITIVE ANODE/MICROCHANNEL PLATE ASSEMBLY. IN AN INCLINED, LOW-EARTH ORBIT, CUPID WILL LOOK UP THE THROAT OF THE CUSP AND MONITOR X-RAYS EMITTED FROM ION INJECTIONS. THE SCIENCE INSTRUMENT AND MUCH OF THE FLIGHT SUBSYSTEMS COME WITH SIGNIFICANT FLIGHT HERITAGE. A PREVIOUS GENERATION OF CUPID S X-RAY TELESCOPE WAS SUCCESSFULLY FLOWN ON THE DXL SOUNDING ROCKET IN 2012. AN IDENTICAL X-RAY TELESCOPE TO THE ONE PLANNED FOR CUPID HAS BEEN DEVELOPED AND WILL FLY ON THE DXL II LAUNCH IN DECEMBER 2015. MANY OF THE FLIGHT SUBSYSTEMS SUCH AS THE FLIGHT RADIO, MAGNETORQUER, POWER SYSTEM, AND FLIGHT COMPUTER WILL BE LEVERAGED FROM THE HIGHLY SUCCESSFUL FIREFLY CUBESAT, CONSTRUCTED AND OPERATED BY TEAM MEMBERS ON PROPOSED PROJECT. THE COMMUNICATION WILL IMPLEMENT A UHF RADIO FOR BOTH UPLINK AND DOWNLINK WITH THE GROUND STATION AT THE NASA WALLOPS FLIGHT FACILITY.
